---
source: crates/openssl-cli/src/tests/help_tests.rs
expression: stdout
---
OpenSSL command-line tool providing cryptographic operations, TLS diagnostics, certificate management, and key generation.

Usage: openssl [COMMAND]

Commands:
  req          Certificate signing request (CSR) operations
  x509         X.509 certificate display, signing, and conversion
  ca           Certificate authority (CA) management
  verify       Certificate chain verification
  crl          Certificate revocation list (CRL) operations
  genpkey      Generate a private key (algorithm-generic)
  pkey         Public or private key utility
  genrsa       Generate an RSA private key
  gendsa       Generate a DSA private key from parameters
  dhparam      Diffie-Hellman parameter generation and management
  dsaparam     DSA parameter generation and management
  rsa          RSA key management utility
  dsa          DSA key management utility
  pkeyparam    Public key algorithm parameter management
  enc          Symmetric cipher encryption and decryption
  dgst         Message digest computation and verification
  pkcs12       PKCS#12 key store operations
  pkcs7        PKCS#7 / CMS-predecessor operations
  pkcs8        PKCS#8 private key format conversion
  smime        S/MIME mail signing, encryption, and verification
  mac          Message Authentication Code (MAC) computation
  kdf          Key Derivation Function (KDF) computation
  pkeyutl      Public key algorithm utility (sign, verify, encrypt, decrypt)
  rsautl       RSA utility (deprecated — use pkeyutl instead)
  passwd       Password hashing utility
  prime        Prime number generation and testing
  rand         Random byte generation
  s_client     TLS/SSL client diagnostic and testing tool
  s_server     TLS/SSL server diagnostic and testing tool
  s_time       TLS connection timing benchmark
  ciphers      Cipher suite listing and information
  sess_id      SSL/TLS session identifier display
  version      Version information display
  list         Algorithm, provider, and capability listing
  speed        Algorithm performance benchmarking
  info         Build and installation information
  errstr       Error code string lookup
  asn1parse    ASN.1 structure parsing and display
  rehash       Certificate directory hash-link management
  skeyutl      Symmetric key utility
  configutl    Configuration file utility
  crl2pkcs7    CRL to PKCS#7 structure conversion
  nseq         Netscape certificate sequence utility
  spkac        Netscape SPKAC operations
  storeutl     URI-based certificate and key store utility
  cms          CMS (Cryptographic Message Syntax) operations
  ocsp         OCSP (Online Certificate Status Protocol) client and responder
  cmp          CMP (Certificate Management Protocol) client operations
  ts           RFC 3161 timestamp authority client
  fipsinstall  FIPS module installation and configuration
  ech          Encrypted Client Hello (ECH) key and config management
  srp          SRP (Secure Remote Password) verifier file management
  ec           Elliptic curve key utility
  ecparam      Elliptic curve parameter generation and management
  help         Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)

Options:
  -h, --help
          Print help (see a summary with '-h')

  -V, --version
          Print version
